addGroup(uint256,address).custom:reverts: DuplicateGroup If the `groupId` already exists in the routing table.NonSequentialGroup If the `groupId` is not the sequentially next group based                 on the known groups.
addGroup(uint256,address).details: It is perfectly valid to add a group with a target address of 0 in order to disable it.While it reverts if the group identifier is not sequential, this is due to the fact      that group identifiers are allocated externally. As a result, they cannot just be      allocated by the router.

params.groupId: The identifier for the new group.
params.groupIdentityManager: The address of the identity manager instance to be used for the        group. If this is set to the null address the group is disabled.

disableGroup(uint256).custom:reverts: NoSuchGroup If the target group does not exist to be disabled.

params.groupId: The identifier for the group to be disabled.

returns.oldTarget: The old target address for the group.

returns.count: The number of groups in the table.

initialize(address).custom:reverts: string If called more than once at the same initalisation number.
initialize(address).details: Must be called exactly once.This is marked `reinitializer()` to allow for updated initialisation steps when working      with upgrades based upon this contract. Be aware that there are only 256 (zero-indexed)      initialisations allowed, so decide carefully when to use them. Many cases can safely be      replaced by use of setters.

params.initialGroupIdentityManager: The address of the identity manager to be used for the        initial group (group ID 0) when instantiating the router.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

routeFor(uint256).custom:reverts: NoSuchGroup If the requested `groupNumber` does not exist.GroupDisabled If the group has been disabled.

params.groupNumber: The number of the group to get the route for.

returns.target: The target address for the group number.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateGroup(uint256,address).custom:reverts: NoSuchGroup If the target group does not exist to be updated.
updateGroup(uint256,address).details: It is perfectly valid to update a group with a target address of 0 in order to disable      it.

params.groupId: The identitifier for the group to have its target address updated.
params.newTargetAddress: The new target address for the group in routing. If this is set to        the null address the group will be disabled.

returns.oldTarget: The old target address for the group.

upgradeTo(address).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

verifyProof(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint.custom:reverts: string If the `proof` is invalid.NoSuchGroup If the provided `groupId` references a group that does not exist.
verifyProof(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint.details: Note that a double-signaling check is not included here, and should be carried by the      caller.

params.externalNullifierHash: A keccak256 hash of the external nullifier
params.groupId: The group identifier for the group to verify a proof for.
params.signalHash: A keccak256 hash of the Semaphore signal
